<p />
<h4><a name="Plan_per_1_4"></a> Plan per 1.4 </h4> <ul>
<li> on next ITB day (3 November) ask Tom to request DNS alias: software-itb to repo-itb
</li> <li> not yet done but can be done at any time
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h4><a name="Plan_per_2_1"></a> Plan per 2.1 </h4> <ul>
<li> on software1 as root: <ul>
<li> cd /usr/local/software-cache
</li> <li> cp -rp {dir_to_copy} /net/nas01/Public/tmp/soft
</li></ul> 
</li></ul> 
<p /> <ul>
<li> on repo1 as root: <ul>
<li> cd /usr/local/repo
</li> <li> cp -rp /net/nas01/Public/tmp/soft/{dir_to_copy} .
</li></ul> 
</li></ul> 
<p /> <ul>
<li> repeat repo1 steps on repo2
</li></ul> 
<p /> <ul>
<li> as of 22 October the following directories on repo-itb should be identical to those on software1 <ul>
<li> /cadist
</li> <li> /debian-repo
</li> <li> /pacman
</li> <li> /yum-repo
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> /osg-1.2 was not copied as it is no longer being referenced
</li> <li> Content on repo-itb may or may not match content on repo1/2, looks like repo-itb has not been updated in some time.
</li> <li> The following (for example) returned identical content: <ul>
<li> wget <a href="http://repo-itb.grid.iu.edu/cadist/ca-certs-version-new" target="_top">http://repo-itb.grid.iu.edu/cadist/ca-certs-version-new</a>
</li> <li> wget <a href="http://software1.grid.iu.edu/cadist/ca-certs-version-new" target="_top">http://software1.grid.iu.edu/cadist/ca-certs-version-new</a>
</li></ul> 
</li></ul> 
